00:01:21.730 --> 00:01:26.470
drain pan under it, to catch anything that drips,
then we'll grab this radiator clamp and

00:01:26.470 --> 00:01:31.450
take the hose out of the way, then we'll get
this old dish pan and stick it here, so you

00:01:31.450 --> 00:01:35.500
can put all the nuts and bolts in and it
won't get lost, then we'll take out the

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:43.390
ignition coils, it just pop right off, you
got wiggle them a little, and then remove

00:01:43.390 --> 00:01:49.420
all the bolts, that hold the valve cover in
place, now here's a trick I learned years

00:01:49.420 --> 00:01:54.730
ago, get a pry bar, put it on the metal on
the head, and then under the valve cover

00:01:54.730 --> 00:01:58.300
here and pry it a little, you can see the
whole thing starts coming up, they stick

00:01:58.300 --> 00:02:02.740
on pretty stuck, and here it is,
