this Lexus gasket is great, it's got

00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:11.680
little ribs in it, so when you put it in
place, it actually snaps and holds itself

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:16.299
in, so when you put it back together, you
don't need to put any glue on it, because

00:02:16.299 --> 00:02:20.680
it'll stay on, since the ridges hold it
in the little groove, then the cover just

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:25.400
goes back on, give it a little push, and then
tighten the valve cover

00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:30.349
gasket bolts, make them snug from the
middle and work your way out till you

00:02:30.349 --> 00:02:34.700
got the outside ones tightened, and then
once you made them all snug, go back and

00:02:34.700 --> 00:02:41.030
make sure they're good and tight, now
these valve cover bolts pretty much up

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:45.500
stops on them, so once they hit the metal, you
can't turn them any more, you just give them a

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:48.829
little bit of a pull, just to make sure
it's as tight as they go, and leave it at

00:02:48.829 --> 00:02:54.829
that, then we put all the coils back on,
and now comes the hard part, we can't

